June, 2018 realmoneypro.thestreet.com/d… For now it seems to me that fundamentals and technicals have given way to The Swan. Black or Orange or hopefully Green, who knows what color but over the short term it is all about which way the Trade talks go.

As I have written over the last year, I remain unambiguously suspicious that a comprehensive agreement will be achieved between the U.S. and China. That said, as far as we have just fallen, I suppose it is possible that we could reverse or quickly change direction on a tweet

or news blip at the most inopportune for everyone. But, I wouldn't count on it. Nevertheless, recent developments in policy underscore the concerns I have had for over a year with regard to the Administration's hostile relationship around the world, in general, and the
President's behavior (crafting policy on the back of a napkin and delivered in a tweet), in particular. Overall, the market continues to underprice risk. realmoney.thestreet.com/doug…
